Information Collection and Use
For a better experience while using our service and/or products, we may require you to provide us with certain personally identifiable information, including but not limited to your name, phone number, and postal address. The information that we collect will be used to contact or identify you.
Personal Information: Personal Information of the users of Ryze App are restricted  to the Ryze App only when voluntarily submitted by the users of Ryze App and we shall use that information for providing services and/or products opted by the user under the Ryze App. We will take all reasonable steps necessary to ensure that user’s data is processed securely and in accordance with this Privacy Policy and applicable law. For the purpose of providing further customized services/products we will ask for certain personal identification information such as your name, email, contact address, Ryze App charging information, computer/mobile browser information, IP address, device and location information, and usage information and pattern etc. (“Personal Information”). We use this information to establish and deliver services and/or products to you. We may use this information to contact registered users to notify them of product and service updates, customized offer, discounts and promotions, provide instructions, and to deliver other service and/or product related information if the user expressly opts in for such sharing/services. We may also contact users to request additional information (location & device details) and feedback. The above-mentioned information provided by the user are stored securely and processed in accordance with this Privacy Policy and applicable laws and regulations.
Log Data: We want to inform you that whenever you visit our App or use our products and/or services, we collect and analyze information that your browser sends to us that is called Log Data. This Log Data may include, but shall not be limited to, information such as your device or computer's Internet Protocol (“IP”) address, web site traffic volume, frequency of visits, browser version, pages of our App that you visit, the time and date of your visit, the time spent on those pages, type and time of transactions, and other statistics. This information is logged to help diagnose technical problems, administer the site, and improve the quality and types of products and services delivered under the App.
Cookies: Cookies are files with small amount of data that is commonly used as an anonymous unique identifier. These are sent to your browser from the website that you visit and are stored on your device or computer’s hard drive. Our website uses these “cookies” to collect information and to improve our service and products. You have the option to either accept or refuse these cookies, and know when a cookie is being sent to your device or computer. If you choose to refuse our cookies, you may not be able to use some portions of our service and/or products.
Service Providers: We may, from time to time, share Personal Information of a user with certain trusted business partners and third party service providers to enable them to facilitate provision of services, perform particular functions such as for marketing /promotion purposes on our behalf in relation to the Ryze App,  if the user expressly opts in to such sharing. Such third parties' processing of user data is subject to security and confidentiality obligations consistent with this Privacy Policy and applicable law. However, they are obligated not to disclose or use the information for any other purpose, other than the purposes for which it has been granted permission.
