Data Storage and Security
We may collect and store your personal data in both electronic and physical forms, depending on the requirement. This information may be stored at our premises or those of third parties, within IT systems such as external cloud storage, internal or third-party management systems, email, databases, hard drives, and document warehouses. We strive, where practicable, to process your personal data in a secure environment, preventing unauthorized or unlawful processing, accidental loss, destruction, or damage to the information. To protect your personal data and our network from unauthorized access, we have implemented various physical, technical, and administrative security measures.
Personal data retention period: We will retain your personal data only for as long as it is necessary for the purposes for which it was collected. The retention period may also be influenced by applicable legal requirements.
Transfers of Personal Data: We may transfer your personal data across geographical borders to other entities in compliance with the law. When your personal data is transferred to our group companies or third parties outside of Bangladesh, we ensure the transfer is conducted under organizational, contractual, and legal measures with adequate protection levels. Additionally, we comply with any local legal requirements to safeguard your personal data for the parties receiving this information
Security: We value your trust in providing us your Personal Information, thus we are striving to use commercially acceptable means of protecting it. However, remember that no method of transmission over the internet, or method of electronic storage is 100% secure and reliable, and we cannot guarantee its absolute security. We have implemented processes designed to protect user information and maintain security. It is the user's responsibility to protect the security of their login information. Our servers are located in secure server environments. Firewalls and other advanced security technologies are employed to prevent interference or access from outside intruders. These safeguards help prevent unauthorized access, maintains data accuracy, and ensures the appropriate use of data.
Opt-Out Procedures
If your personally identifiable information changes, or if you no longer desire to use Ryze App’s services and/or products, you can correct or update your personally identifiable information, or deactivate your accounts by using Ryze App platform. Inquiries on such changes can be directed to support@ryze.live
Delete Account: The "Delete Account" feature of Ryze App can be initiated by users themselves through the hamburger Menu. The "Delete Account" option is conveniently located within the Hamburger Menu. Upon selecting the "Delete account" option, a 'Double Consent' page will appear, requiring users to confirm their decision. Upon confirmation, the user will be restricted from using Ryze App for a specified period, currently set at 30 minutes. Once this time elapses, users can resume using Ryze App as a new user. This action will delete the user's data history. It is important to note that, the user is not permanently removed from the system; instead, a soft deletion is implemented and the same user will not be considered for ‘Sign-Up’ Bonus.
